padding.enumval: 0 / 1 0x1000 Change in direction of phase rotation

padding.desc: 2 6 Metering function or metering function PLUS
0 4 Switch user output mode to trip message
Status of user output mode 1 = 0 Trip is output 0 5 =1 Actuation by user
0 7 Read status of user input (COM16 only)

padding.enumval: 48 49 TV long-time mean value for current
48 49 TV long-time mean value for current
56 57 TV long-time mean value for active power
56 57 TV long-time mean value for active power
58 59 TV long-time mean value for apparent power
58 59 TV long-time mean value for apparent power
60 61 TV long-time mean value for reactive power
60 61 TV long-time mean value for reactive power
62 63 TV reactive power in normal direction
62 63 TV reactive power in normal direction
64 65 TV reactive power in reverse direction
64 65 TV reactive power in reverse direction
84 85 TV active power in normal direction
- 84 85 TV active power in normal direction
86 87 TV active power in reverse direction
- 86 87 TV active power in reverse direction
30 = Change in phase dir. of rot.
0 2 Circuit breaker has tripped (trip alarm switch)

padding.desc: I2t characteristic for short-time delayed overcurrent

padding.enumval: 0 0 I2t characteristic for delayed short-circuit protection switched off (default).
0 1 I2t characteristic for delayed short-circuit protection switched on.
0 0 I2t characteristic for ground-fault protection switched off (default).
0 1 I2t characteristic for ground-fault protection switched on.
0 0 I4t characteristic for long-time/overload protection switched off (default).
0 1 I4t characteristic for overload protection switched on.
0 0 No maintenance necessary yet on main contacts Note:Despite this, the main contacts must be checked after every overcurrent tripping operation.
0 1 Perform immediate visual inspection on main contacts.
0 2 Prepare maintenance of the main contacts.
0 / 1 0x0002 Delete last trip message in trip unit
0 / 1 0x0022 Reset counter and statistical information of the trip unit
0 0 GF sensing with external iron-core CT
0 1 GF sensing via residual method (vector summation)
